<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870414-0108 </DOCNO><HL> Canada Plans SalesOf $1 Billion of Bonds</HL><DD> 04/14/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CANDABOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><DATELINE> OTTAWA  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Canadian government said it will offer $1 billion (Canadian) of bonds in three issues this week.    The sales will include 8.5% bonds due March 1992, 8.75% bonds due June 1996 and 9% bonds due March 2011. Terms will be announced today.    The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least $100 million of the bonds, including at least $5 million of the 2011 issue. The rest will be available to the public.    Proceeds will be used to redeem $650 million of bonds maturing May 1 and for general government purposes. </TEXT></DOC>